data.text:
Rasheed Wallace - Points

Rasheed Wallace scores a career high 42 points (2001)

On February 20, 2001, Rasheed Wallace set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 42 points in Portland's home win against Denver, 104-94. He also had 7 rebounds, 4 assists, 1 steal and 2 blocks. He shot 13/20 from two, 4/7 from three, shooting at 63.0% from the field. He also shot 4/5 from the free-throw line.

Rasheed Wallace - Rebounds

Rasheed Wallace grabs a career high 18 rebounds (2001)

On January 01, 2001, Rasheed Wallace set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 18 rebounds in Portland's home win against Charlotte, 89-67. He also had 12 points, 3 assists, 2 steals and 2 blocks.

Rasheed Wallace - Assists

Rasheed Wallace gives a career high 8 assists (2003)

On December 18, 2003, Rasheed Wallace set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 8 assists in Portland's home win against Phoenix, 101-94. He also had 15 points, 7 rebounds and 3 blocks.

Rasheed Wallace - Steals

Rasheed Wallace has a career high 6 steals (2010)

On March 10, 2010, Rasheed Wallace tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 6 steals in Boston's home loss against Memphis, 91-111. He also had 11 points, 2 rebounds.

Rasheed Wallace - Blocks

Rasheed Wallace blocks a career high 6 shots (2008)

On November 01, 2008, Rasheed Wallace tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 6 blocks in Detroit's home win against Washington, 117-109. He also had 17 points, 12 rebounds and 2 assists.

Rasheed Wallace - Efficiency

Rasheed Wallace records a career high 47 efficiency rating (2003)

On January 15, 2003, Rasheed Wallace set his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 47 efficiency in Portland's home win against Memphis, 100-92. He also had 38 points, 10 rebounds and 3 assists.
